    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Change H and L Keys in Vimperator]]></title>
    <link href="http://stephentseng.com/blog/2013/06/10/change-h-and-l-keys-in-vimperator/"/>
    <updated>2013-06-10T18:34:00-04:00</updated>
    <id>http://stephentseng.com/blog/2013/06/10/change-h-and-l-keys-in-vimperator</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I have used Firefox plug-in Vimperator for a while. The default shortcut of back and forward is <code>shift + H</code> and <code>shift + L</code> in Vimperator. I found it is not efficiency enough to type two keys. I added two lines to <code>vimrc</code> file:</p>

<pre><code>noremap h &lt;S-h&gt;
noremap l &lt;S-l&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>With this setting, I can just type H or L key once to back or forward.</p>
]]></content>
